CatDescriptText: Edith Johnson is the daughter of photographer Luther Johnson and pianist Maudelena Johnson.  Vivian Davidson Hewitt is the first African American president of the Special Libraries Association and an art collector.
TitMainTitle: University of Pittsburgh students Edith Johnson, Mary Louise Wray Stewart, Esther Dalton, and Mary Jane Mitchell Page, on steps of Cathedral of Learning, with Pearl Johnson Hairston, Geraldine, and Jacqueline Ford in background
